o be some\nunnecessary confu=\r\nsion. A few pointers:\n&gt; \n&gt; 1. There are various sacred chants embedded with=\r\nin the Vedas, Puranas,\nAgamas etc. Broadly speaking such sacred chants can =\r\nbe categorised as\nmantras, stotras, kavachas, dhyanams etc. Some stotras to=\r\no are also treated\nas mahamantras and mantras. The Samhita portion of the V=\r\nedas too is referred\nto as mantras.\n&gt; \n&gt; 2. Undoubtedly mantras and stotras=\r\n have to be chanted in the original.\nReading a translation is not even comp=\r\narable to chanting the original chant.\nSo far it is fine.\n&gt; \n&gt; 3. Whilst ma=\r\nntra, stotra and kavacha are all based on Sabda/Vak, tradition\nmakes a dist=\r\ninction between them.\n&gt; \n&gt; 4. As per the traditional view one doesn&#39;t need =\r\nto be initiated to chant a\nstotra or dhyanam. The case is not the same with=\r\n most mantras. Mantras\ncontaining bijaksharas, agamic mantras, mantras of M=\r\nahavidyas etc need\ninitiation. This is the traditional view. Mantras from t=\r\nhe Veda Samhita are\nnot the same as these other mantras that need initiatio=\r\nn, which are\ngenerally referred to as Agamic/Tantrik mantras. Whatever you =\r\ncall these\nmantras the actual idea is that these mantras are integral parts=\r\n of larger\nand distinct spiritual specialities that need initiation, as in =\r\nthe case of\nMahavidyas such as Kali or Sri.\n&gt; \n&gt; 5. Vishnusahasranama, Siva=\r\nsahasranama, Aditya hrdayam etc do not need\ninitiation as they fall under s=\r\ntotra category only. Lalitasahasranama and\nDevi Mahatmyam are traditionally=\r\n viewed not MERELY as stotras or parts of\npuranas. They have a larger statu=\r\ns as integral parts of a Mahavidya sadhana.\nChanting them without initiatio=\r\nn is not recommended especially when the\nreader combines the navarna or sho=\r\ndashi mantras too as an integral part of\nthe chanting.\n&gt; \n&gt; 6. I know from =\r\npersonal interaction that acharyas belonging to both Kanchi\nas well as Srin=\r\ngeri paramparas recommend initiation for both the sadhanas of\nSri Sri Chand=\r\ni and Sri Vidya along with their respective NAVAKSHARI AND\nSHODASAKSHARI ma=\r\nntras which are treated as an INTEGRAL LIMB (ANGA) of the\nsadhana. Acharyas=\r\n of both these traditions hold that one needs to be\ninitiated to chant the =\r\nNavarna as well as shodashakshari mantras.\n&gt; \n&gt; 7. Recapping my earlier sta=\r\nnce, Devi Mahatmyam is a great text that has an\nindependent status by itsel=\r\nf as part of a Mahavidya. It is simultaneously a\nMahavidya, a Yogasastra as=\r\n well as an Advaitic text in the spirit of the\nUpanishads. ***As a Mahavidy=\r\na the Navakshari is an integral part of Sri Sri\nChandi path***. Thus tradit=\r\nion holds that one needs to be initiated to chant\nit. However if one wishes=\r\n to benefit from the Yoga-Vedanta or Sacred myth\naspects of the Devi Mahatm=\r\nyam, , reading the sacred myth in the vernacular\nhas been recommended in my=\r\n write-up, as chanting the original along with the\nnavakshari amounts to pr=\r\nacticing the sadhana of a Mahavidya. In that case it\nis recommended to be i=\r\nnitiated and go through the specialised sadhanas\nproperly under guidance.\n&gt;=\r\n \n&gt; 8. Arguably if an uninitiated person reads the Devi Mahatmyam in the\nor=\r\niginal Sanskrit as part of the *Pauranik* approach and not as a Mahavidya,\n=\r\nit has an inherent problem in our times. The problem with attempting to do =\r\na\nparayana of Devi Mahatmyam from texts alone (without initiation) is that\n=\r\nmost readers inadvertently end up also chanting the Navarna mantra or\nstotr=\r\nas such as the Siddhakunjika stotram which too contain the bijaksharas.\n&gt; \n=\r\n&gt; 9. I you carefully peruse my write-up on the Devi Mahatmyam, forget\ntrans=\r\nlating, nowhere do I put down the Navarna mantra even in writing.\nNeither h=\r\nave I attempted to write a commentary on it. Translations of\nmantras do not=\r\n have the power of the original mantra as Sabda or Vak.\nHowever it is recom=\r\nmended to know the essence or import (artha) of the\nmantra and its sadhana =\r\nwhile chanting it. Infact `artha&#39; is the import, the\nessence of `Vak&#39;, not =\r\na translation! \n&gt; \n&gt; 10. For those who are already doing Sri Sri Chandi pat=\r\nh without\ninitiation, there is no need to worry or be confused. There has t=\r\no be a\ncertain level of samskara to be attracted to Sri Sri Chandi path its=\r\nelf. We\nall have it. Otherwise we would not be doing it (initiation or no\ni=\r\nnitiation). Please keep doing whatever you are doing. Just be cautious not\n=\r\nto do sakama sadhana. As Narasimha garu has rightly pointed out it is bette=\r\nr\nto just do the sadhana WITHOUT asking for any favours or results. That\nat=\r\ntitude itself will reduce a lot of the potential problem. Things will\nhappe=\r\nn on their own accord in the natural flow. Leave the rest to the\ncompassion=\r\nate Goddess. \n&gt; \n&gt; Hope the above pointers help in clearing any confusion. =\r\n\n&gt; \n&gt; Regards,\n&gt; Satya Prakash \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=\r\n=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; --- In vedic=\r\n-wisdom@yahoogroups.com\n&lt;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&gt; , h ramalin=\r\ngam &lt;hramalingam@&gt; wrote:\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Namaste everybody\n&gt; &gt; I want to share one=\r\n anecdote happened in front of Kanchi Maha Sannidanam\nSri\n&gt; &gt; Sri Chandrase=\r\nkara Bharathi Swamigal\n&gt; &gt; When Swamigal was staying in a camp near Mysore =\r\nin Karnataka One day all\nthe\n&gt; &gt; learned persons male and female alike\n&gt; &gt; =\r\nrequested Swamigal to translate Sri Vishnu SahasraNamam in kannada\nlanguage=\r\n\n&gt; &gt; so that they can chant knowing the meaning fully.\n&gt; &gt; Swamigal didn&#39;t =\r\nreply to this request which was made early in the\nmorning.\n&gt; &gt; Later in the=\r