xt&gt;\n\n&lt;p =\r\nstyle=3D&#39;margin-bottom:12.0pt&#39;&gt;Namaste Satya Prakash ji,&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIt was ve=\r\nry nice to see your email and especially point No.10.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIs it possib=\r\nle to clarify point no.8? If it can be revealed in this open forum,\nplease =\r\nenligten us as to what are those &quot;potential dangers&quot; which has\nfo=\r\nrced traditions to strongly recommend &quot;Initiation&quot; for\nDeviMahatm=\r\nyam.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nWarm Regards,&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nUtpal&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n--- In &lt;a href=3D&quot;mailt=\r\no:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/a&gt;,\n&quot;D=\r\nr Satya Prakash&quot; &lt;backtocosmicroots@...&gt; wrote:&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt=\r\n; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Namaste friends,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Essentially I agr=\r\nee with Narasimha garu in most matters in this\ndiscussion. The only major p=\r\noint where I disagree is whether one can do Sri Sri\nChandi path *without in=\r\nitiation*. The rest of the confusion on translation of\nmantras needs some c=\r\nlarification as there seems to be some unnecessary\nconfusion. A few pointer=\r\ns:&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 1. There are various sacred chants embedded within th=\r\ne Vedas, Puranas,\nAgamas etc. Broadly speaking such sacred chants can be ca=\r\ntegorised as mantras,\nstotras, kavachas, dhyanams etc. Some stotras too are=\r\n also treated as\nmahamantras and mantras. The Samhita portion of the Vedas =\r\ntoo is referred to as\nmantras.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 2. Undoubtedly mantras an=\r\nd stotras have to be chanted in the original.\nReading a translation is not =\r\neven comparable to chanting the original chant. So\nfar it is fine.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 3. Whilst mantra, stotra and kavacha are all based on Sabda/Vak,=\r\n tradition\nmakes a distinction between them.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 4. As per t=\r\nhe traditional view one doesn&#39;t need to be initiated to chant a\nstotra or d=\r\nhyanam. The case is not the same with most mantras. Mantras\ncontaining bija=\r\nksharas, agamic mantras, mantras of Mahavidyas etc need\ninitiation. This is=\r\n the traditional view. Mantras from the Veda Samhita are not\nthe same as th=\r\nese other mantras that need initiation, which are generally\nreferred to as =\r\nAgamic/Tantrik mantras. Whatever you call these mantras the\nactual idea is =\r\nthat these mantras are integral parts of larger and distinct\nspiritual spec=\r\nialities that need initiation, as in the case of Mahavidyas such\nas Kali or=\r\n Sri.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 5. Vishnusahasranama, Sivasahasranama, Aditya hrda=\r\nyam etc do not need initiation\nas they fall under stotra category only. Lal=\r\nitasahasranama and Devi Mahatmyam\nare traditionally viewed not MERELY as st=\r\notras or parts of puranas. They have a\nlarger status as integral parts of a=\r\n Mahavidya sadhana. Chanting them without\ninitiation is not recommended esp=\r\necially when the reader combines the navarna\nor shodashi mantras too as an =\r\nintegral part of the chanting.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 6. I know from personal i=\r\nnteraction that acharyas belonging to both Kanchi\nas well as Sringeri param=\r\nparas recommend initiation for both the sadhanas of\nSri Sri Chandi and Sri =\r\nVidya along with their respective NAVAKSHARI AND\nSHODASAKSHARI mantras whic=\r\nh are treated as an INTEGRAL LIMB (ANGA) of the\nsadhana. Acharyas of both t=\r\nhese traditions hold that one needs to be initiated to\nchant the Navarna as=\r\n well as shodashakshari mantras.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 7. Recapping my earlier=\r\n stance, Devi Mahatmyam is a great text that has an\nindependent status by i=\r\ntself as part of a Mahavidya. It is simultaneously a\nMahavidya, a Yogasastr=\r\na as well as an Advaitic text in the spirit of the\nUpanishads. ***As a Maha=\r\nvidya the Navakshari is an integral part of Sri Sri\nChandi path***. Thus tr=\r\nadition holds that one needs to be initiated to chant\nit. However if one wi=\r\nshes to benefit from the Yoga-Vedanta or Sacred myth aspects\nof the Devi Ma=\r\nhatmyam, , reading the sacred myth in the vernacular has been\nrecommended i=\r\nn my write-up, as chanting the original along with the navakshari\namounts t=\r\no practicing the sadhana of a Mahavidya. In that case it is\nrecommended to =\r\nbe initiated and go through the specialised sadhanas properly\nunder guidanc=\r\ne.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 8. Arguably if an uninitiated person reads the Devi M=\r\nahatmyam in the\noriginal Sanskrit as part of the *Pauranik* approach and no=\r\nt as a Mahavidya, it\nhas an inherent problem in our times. The problem with=\r\n attempting to do a\nparayana of Devi Mahatmyam from texts alone (without in=\r\nitiation) is that most\nreaders inadvertently end up also chanting the Navar=\r\nna mantra or stotras such\nas the Siddhakunjika stotram which too contain th=\r\ne bijaksharas.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 9. I you carefully peruse my write-up on =\r\nthe Devi Mahatmyam, forget\ntranslating, nowhere do I put down the Navarna m=\r\nantra even in writing. Neither\nhave I attempted to write a commentary on it=\r\n. Translations of mantras do not\nhave the power of the original mantra as S=\r\nabda or Vak. However it is\nrecommended to know the essence or import (artha=\r\n) of the mantra and its sadhana\nwhile chanting it. Infact `artha&#39; is the im=\r\nport, the essence of `Vak&#39;, not a\ntranslation! &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 10. For =\r\nthose who are already doing Sri Sri Chandi path without\ninitiation, there i=\r\ns no need to worry or be confused. There has to be a certain\nlevel of samsk=\r\nara to be attracted to Sri Sri Chandi path itself. We all have\nit. Otherwis=\r\ne we would not be doing it (initiation or no initiation). Please\nkeep doing=\r\n whatever you are doing. Just be cautious not to do sakama sadhana.\nAs Nara=\r\nsimha garu has rightly pointed out it is better to just do the sadhana\nWITH=\r\nOUT asking for any favours or results. That attitude itself will reduce a\nl=\r\not of the potential problem. Things will happen on their own accord in the\n=\r\nnatural flow. Leave the rest to the compassionate Goddess. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt; Hope the above pointers help in clearing any confusion. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; Regards,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Satya Prakash &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt=\r\n; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=\r\n=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; --- In &lt;a href=3D&quot;mailto:ve=\r\ndic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/a&gt;,\nh ramalinga=\r\nm &lt;hramalingam@&gt; wrote:&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; Namaste everybody=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; I want to share one anecdote happened in front of Kanchi Mah=\r\na\nSannidanam Sri\n(Message over 64 KB, truncated)"}}